Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is a perovskite-type oxide that exhibits excellent mixed ionic-electronic conducting properties and is a suitable cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: This study investigates the microstructural, optical, mechanical, and electrical properties of an LSCF-samarium-doped ceria (SDC) composite cathode.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: LSCF-SDC composite cathode powders were prepared by mixing 50 wt% SDC electrolyte with LSCF cathode powders obtained by the rotary evaporation technique.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: The band gap of the prepared powders was determined via diffuse reflectance UV-visible spectroscopy.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: The chemical composition, mechanical properties, and electrochemical properties of the sintered pellets were characterized using Raman spectroscopy, Vickers hardness, and impedance spectroscopy, respectively.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction and Rietveld analysis showed that phase purity was only 96%.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: Moreover, a small fraction of tetragonal phase impurity was observed on the LSCF powders.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: Impurities significantly affected the phase stability and microstructure of the LSCF-SDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: The addition of the SDC electrolyte enhanced the densification of the composite cathode, thereby improving mechanical properties.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: However, the addition of SDC exerted different effects on the DC electrical conductivity and area-specific resistance (ASR) of the composite cathode.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: At 800 A degrees C, the ASR value of the LSCF was only 2% that of the LSCF-SDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique

Sentencas: Overall, the electrical properties of the LSCF-SDC composite cathode are closely related to the crystal structure, purity, and microstructure of LSCF cathode powders.
Titulo: Optical, mechanical and electrical properties of LSCF-SDC composite cathode prepared by sol-gel assisted rotary evaporation technique
